Crude: The Real Price of Oil

Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Joe Berlinger, published by Entendre Films in 2011 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Crude: The Real Price of Oil
Three years in the making, this cinÃƒÂ©ma-vÃƒÂ©ritÃƒÂ© feature from acclaimed filmmaker Joe Berlinger (Brother's Keeper, Paradise Lost, Metallica: Some Kind of Monster) is the epic story of one of the largest and most controversial legal cases on the planet. An inside look at the infamous $27 billion &quot;Amazon Chernobyl&quot; case, Crude is a real-life high stakes legal drama set against a backdrop of the environmental movement, global politics, celebrity activism, human rights advocacy, the media, multinational corporate power, and rapidly-disappearing indigenous cultures. Presenting a complex situation from multiple viewpoints, the film subverts the conventions of advocacy filmmaking as it examines a complicated situation from all angles while bringing an important story of environmental peril and human suffering into focus.

